observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor/in-charge of Solid Waste Management:

Intensify the “no segregation, no collection policy” among the residents of the Municipality;

Enforce strict implementation of the provisions of Sections 21 and 22 of RA 9003 on the mandatory segregation of solid wastes and carry out the following:

Strengthen Information and Education Campaign activities like information dissemination relative to solid waste management;

Establish close coordination with barangay officials to ensure that efforts to improve the SWM will reach the constituents at the barangay level;

Develop a strategic scheme, like providing incentives, for the purpose of encouraging constituents or enterprises to develop or undertake responsible and effective solid waste management; and

Impose fines and penalties for any offense made or violation of Section 48 of RA 9003.

Ensure the establishment or maintenance of MRF in all barangays pursuant to Section 32 of RA 9003; and

Construct and operate a sanitary landfill as a final disposal site for solid wastes to ensure protection of public health and the environment.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
Instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to:
a.1 Verify in their records by tracing the history of these bank accounts, conduct investigation and come up with a course of action based on the result of their validation;
a.2 Immediately coordinate with the LBP and request a certification confirming the existence or non-existence of the eight CIB accounts of the Municipality;
a.3	In case the existence of these CIB accounts cannot be confirmed, prepare adjusting entries to remove these accounts in the books; and
Henceforth, ensure to conduct regular reconciliation of all bank reports vis-à-vis the book balances to ascertain the correctness and existence of all CIB accounts recorded in the financial statements.
